{{M|Lagavulin Matriarch||2}} is a {{2|Bosses|Boss}} found in the {{2|Underdocks}}.

== Pattern ==
{{Intents|Lagavulin Matriarch|2}}
The {{M|Lagavulin Matriarch||2}} starts {{BD|Asleep||2}} with 12 {{BD|Plating||2}}. It sleeps for 3 turns or until it takes unblocked damage, whichever comes first. When it wakes up, it loses its {{BD|Plating||2}}.

After waking, it repeats this four-move cycle:
# {{Int|Lagavulin Matriarch|Slash||2}}
# {{Int|Lagavulin Matriarch|Disembowel||2}}
# {{Int|Lagavulin Matriarch|Slash2||2}}
# {{Int|Lagavulin Matriarch|Soul Siphon||2}}

* Waking the {{M|Lagavulin Matriarch||2}} early (by dealing unblocked damage) removes its {{BD|Plating||2}} immediately, but also ends the free setup turns.
* {{Int|Lagavulin Matriarch|Soul Siphon||2}} permanently reduces the player's {{BD|Strength||2}} and {{BD|Dexterity||2}} by 2 each cycle, making long fights increasingly punishing.
==Trivia==
{{M|Lagavulin Matriarch||2}}'s appearance, abilities, and name are a reference to the {{M|Lagavulin||1}} elite from Slay the Spire 1.
